name: Pearllyn Quek Urology and Bladder Control Centre

reviews.text: Dr Quek is a good urologist. She was able to diagnose the issue and explain it well to me.

Doctor Quek is a doctor with a big heart. She treated my issues professionally and was very kind to me. Since, my condition has improved so much. I thank God for doctors like her, who really make a difference in the lives of others.

Definitely one of the most professional, ethical and patient private practitioners I’ve experienced for my chronic uti issues. For a condition that a highly raved urologist previously deemed as “no other solution for me”, Dr Quek managed to reassess my condition and offered me different perspectives. She patiently analysed my 2 full pages of medical journal on our first consultation and treated me accordingly based on her initial prognosis since then. I feel very much at ease under her care. Really thankful to have found her and that truly gave me hope towards the road to recovery. Wish we have met earlier to save me from the agony.

Dr Quek is very experienced and thorough. Her diagnosis is on point, supported by evidence via tests. She is always many steps ahead of the problem. She patiently answers all my questions, goes through each detail and leaves no stones unturned. I am very blessed to have found her. Her sense of humour makes the consultation less tense too. She has a caring team in Sai Gek, Ann,  Amy & Vanessa supporting her.

Dr Quek is a trusted urologist, having helped my life gain normalcy, managing my condition successfully and always going above and beyond to offer advice, troubleshooting on adjacent areas of the body which in turn affects her focus areas. She transparently communicates options and works to develop a sustainable treatment plan.
